## Summary of design and brand recommendations

The Bonneval identity should feel like **the quiet confidence of Berry Bros & Rudd, the exclusive access of Corney & Barrow, the heritage suggestion of TWG Tea, and the gallery-not-store aesthetic of the art world** — all distilled into a brand that is unmistakably its own. Every touchpoint whispers rather than shouts. The constraint of ten domaines is the brand's greatest asset: it forces focus, enables depth, and communicates a curatorial eye that broader merchants cannot match.

The website should load slowly and beautifully, like entering a cellar. The WhatsApp messages should read like personal notes from a trusted advisor. The printed materials should feel like something worth keeping. And the wines themselves — presented with the reverence of artworks, the precision of investment instruments, and the warmth of something shared between friends — should make every member feel they have been invited into a world most people will never see.